<br />

<br />
Everyone else talks about building a hotkey with &quot;/stopsong&quot; in it.  It is not necessary to waste a hotkey on that.  They recently, within the last patch or two, created a mappable function to that for people on horses that were unable to duck.  Now I know that ducking does squat for bards but this function acts just like /stopsong.  You can find it where you set your keys for your spell casting under the name of something like &quot;Stop casting&quot;.  I mapped mine to keypad-'.' (since I twist with my keypad) and now with n52 macro just briefly tap that before my next song.  Works like a charm for autotwist macros or for single tap twisting manually with the n52 (put the numpad-'.' prior to the song start).
<br />

<br />
Hope that yall find this useful.  I don't have access to the concert hall but if someone does and thinks it's useful feel free to pos this there too.  Happy barding to you on your n5x's!  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Luni Toones - Lvl66/AA38/GL18
Vallon Zek - Xanit K'Ven</span></td>
