				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nostromo game pad<a name="63534"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 22 04 8:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It does help a lot for 2boxing, I also box a cleric but I use the N52 for my bard with my left hand and heal on the other keyboard with my right. There are 3 seperate profiles with the N52 and you can map a button to switch between them (the 3 lights by the thumb button) I've found that this is probably the most useful feature of them all. Once you learn how to use this quickly, there is no limit to  how many functions you can map, it's awesome. I had a hard time at first trying to keep it comfortable and still covering all my funtions, I don't use twist macros so I need even more buttons for each song. I don't use /stopsong, I just tap a song again to interrupt, this keeps it close to using the keyboard like I used to, IMO. Using the N52 has probably helped me the most by making it easier for me to keep 4 songs up consistently (minus lag) and it has helped my cc immensely. I really push this on folks who have a hard time with targeting, instrument juggling and holding mezzes while keeping a twist. From my experience the N52 has tightened all of those areas up because I don't even have to move my left hand, just my fingers. I keep mouse look on and use the right button to look around. 
<br />
</span></td>
