				<td colspan="2"><span>I use it and love it.  In EQ I map all hotbuttons to F1-F10.  In nostromo I map from the lower buttons from right to left F1-F4 and setup cast 1-4 hotbuttons to stop and cast gems 1-4. The fifth one I use to sit (should probably change but I am used to it).
<br />

<br />
I have F5 mapped to the first right button on the top set of keyboard buttons, and then use the rest for targetting and stuff.
<br />

<br />
Being able to move with my left hand thumb and twist with my left hand fingers is great since I use the mouse for mouse look etc.
<br />

<br />
edit: I also programmed the throttle to auto-twist songs 1 - 4.  I used to use this for AE a lot.  I could use it to chant kite, but I find chant kiting boring.   In grouping I found it totally unreliable because of 1) missed notes and 2) I can't stop the macro mid way through....If I have to mez, slow or do anything else during the macro I have to wait for it to finish.</span></td>
